text: The New Jersey Senate is the upper house of the New Jersey Legislature by the Constitution of 1844, replacing the Legislative Council. There are 40 legislative districts. Each district has one senator and two members of the New Jersey General Assembly, the lower house of the legislature. ==Other websites== *New Jersey Legislature Homepage *New Jersey Senate Bill Search *New Jersey section of Project Vote Smart, a national database of voting records and other information about legislators. *Senate Democratic Office *Senate Republican Office Category:New Jersey Category:State upper houses in the United States
